  "notes": "The AV does not publish an average-salary-by-age-and-service exhibit directly. Exhibit C \u2013 Part III (report page 35, PDF page 46) publishes total lives (counts) and total annual salaries by age and service. Source table index 1 holds the total annual salary dollars per cell; source table index 0 holds the corresponding member counts (used as weights). Average salary per cell = total salary / count, which deterministic code must compute; I transcribe the raw salary totals (table 1) and counts (table 0) and declare weighted_avg for rows using counts as weights. Column 'sum' ops aggregate salary totals and (with counts as weights) counts so per-cell averages are recomputed correctly. Target '<25' combines 'Under 20' and '20 to 24'; target '64' maps to source '60 to 63' (top age band limited by mandatory retirement at 63); target row '70' has no source data (no members above age 63) so empty sources. Column '40' maps to source '35 and over'. Total rows/columns excluded from cells but recorded in printed totals. Empty cells kept null. No suppressed '*' cells present. Both count and salary cell layouts verified against printed row and column totals."
}